div.div:
Add Pusher push notifications for Laravel
This commit integrates Pusher's native push notifications for the Laravel framework. Several new configuration files have been added for Pusher and the Laravel Notification Channels. This allows the user to send push notifications using Laravel's built-in functions following the Pusher's standards, making it possible to unify the coding style across various editors and IDEs.

Add push notifications option to footer
In footer.blade.php, a clickable text has been added that enables push notifications when clicked by the user. A corresponding 'enableNotifications' function has been introduced in app.js to handle the logic of push notification registrations.

Implement push notifications and clean up code
Implemented Pusher Beams for push notifications, adding necessary code blocks to app.js, including a new 'service-worker.js' file, and a script reference to app.blade.php. To ensure cleaner and more readable code, unnecessary whitespace in 'app.js' was also removed.

Integrate Pusher library and expand report functionalities
This commit integrates the Pusher library into the application and expands report functionalities. A new script reference to Pusher was added to "app.blade.php". New classes "TestReport", "ReportReview", and "AttachmentReportReview" were added to handle reporting tasks. Pusher is also initialized in "app.js" with connection status monitoring. Adjustments were also made in "broadcasting.php" to set the Pusher server location to 'eu'.

Refactor config and enhance code readability
The code commits mainly refactor several configuration codes and enhance the readability of some parts of the code. The Pusher port and protocol in the broadcasting configuration have been made configurable. Moreover, the Redis host in the database configuration has been set to use an environment variable. Also, code readability has been improved by using full namespaced import statements in several controllers.
